    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Sound of Gunfire in America</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Daniel Schmutter letter on calls for sweeping new gun laws; observes that criminals will neither obtain licenses nor register their weapons</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your Sept. 5 editorial calls for sweeping new gun laws, including licensing and registration of all gun owners.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your Sept. 5 editorial calls for sweeping new gun laws, including licensing and registration of all gun owners.</p>
        <p>Of course, criminals will neither obtain licenses nor register their guns. Nor will they use trigger locks, limit street purchases to one gun per month or wait three days. The ability of criminals to obtain their tools of trade will be unaffected.</p>
        <p>How will any of these proposed measures address the terrible statistics you cite? This problem is never discussed by gun control proponents, because there is no relationship at all between the problem identified and the solutions proposed.</p>
        <p>DANIEL SCHMUTTER  West Orange, N.J., Sept. 5, 2000</p>
      </block>
